'''Adtwifyrdi''' is the name used by the [[Venerable Bede]] to describe the meeting of [[river]] and [[tributary]] at the mouth of the [[River Aln]], at [[Alnmouth]], [[Northumberland]]. <ref>[http://www.alnmouth.org.uk/Church/2.htm Church of St. John the Baptist, Alnmouth, Alnwick, Northumberland<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

